Thinking about making a bot, who will run over to where you click.
The idea is the cursor is always 0,0
When you click, it calls pos and goes to the spot the character is at,
If it moves right, we simply print space and the char,
then move back to 0,0
However, left, down and up are more complex
We have to remove the old char, place the new one and then move back to 0,0
And then we come to actually determning movement
That's just some math, and then sometimes randomly choosing to go some way two or three times

