I need to add both a range() function, to make a list of numbers
Just list Python does :D
It wont actually be that useful for a for loop in this language
The reason being, if you use range, this is what it would look like:

for (let i = 0; i < len(range(5)); i++){
  print(i);
}

Vs.

for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++){
  print(i);
}

The second one uses less code, it's more readable, and it doesn't
require a function call to get a number.
It's also more memory efficient, since it doesn't have to store
the list of numbers in memory.
This is especially useful, since C++ isn't memory safe.
So, I need to also add a del function, to delete a variable
Or, I could just make it so that when the variable goes out of scope,
it gets deleted automatically.
While and for wouldn't be considered scope, since I want to keep my idea of
using while to wait for a mouse input before doing anything else
I could make it to where there's a main function named main()
And to keep Minis memory safe.. If you're smart about using functions,
it will return anything it has to return.. If anything at all, and then,
it deletes every variable that was used inside it.
The guide will discourage having anything but the main game loop,
to avoid having any extra variables in memory.

Maybe, I remove the Input. in the source code, and make Input an actual library.
