I've also thought about security implementations, such as an encoded sha256 hash of the code. The runner will generate a hash (Removing the hash info first of course), and make sure it matches the included hash.
Although, this is likely pointless, as byte written code isn't human-readable, and there aren't features that can damage a computer.
The name will also have the first four characters of a hash of the entire compiled minis file.
This is to ensure the naming convention is unique.

